Owen, this is my daughter, Izzy.

01:21:12.240 --> 01:21:13.514
Hello.

01:21:13.600 --> 01:21:16.638
Can you fix Mr. Church's cough?

01:21:18.040 --> 01:21:20.350
I will certainly give it my all.

01:21:24.640 --> 01:21:27.029
You know, maybe I shouldn't go.

01:21:27.120 --> 01:21:28.838
You're still sick.

01:21:28.920 --> 01:21:30.479
I'm fine.

01:21:30.560 --> 01:21:33.632
And I know where to find
a doctor if I need one.

01:21:40.640 --> 01:21:42.551
Well?

01:21:42.640 --> 01:21:44.711
You're so beautiful, Mama.

01:21:46.320 --> 01:21:48.391
Mr. Church, tell her.

01:21:51.920 --> 01:21:53.752
True vision, my dear.

01:21:57.000 --> 01:22:00.197
So, Owen Baxter became a doctor.

01:22:00.280 --> 01:22:03.910
You're the one who told me
to do something good with my life.

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:05.229
I thought by now...

01:22:05.320 --> 01:22:07.880
you'd be a very serious novelist...

01:22:07.960 --> 01:22:09.997
living in Boston.

01:22:10.080 --> 01:22:13.516
I guess life
had other plans for me.

01:22:20.920 --> 01:22:22.479
Izzy?

01:22:22.560 --> 01:22:24.471
Izzy.

01:22:26.280 --> 01:22:28.590
Tell me about her father.

01:22:31.960 --> 01:22:33.792
Did you love him?

01:22:36.200 --> 01:22:39.113
It was just a foolish night.

01:22:39.200 --> 01:22:44.070
Guess you could say I was
a little lost after Mama died.

01:22:44.160 --> 01:22:46.959
He didn't want to have
anything to do with the baby.

01:22:48.480 --> 01:22:50.630
But he gave me
the greatest gift.

01:22:55.000 --> 01:22:57.719
I tried finding you for a few years.

01:22:57.800 --> 01:22:59.473
You found me now.

01:23:02.520 --> 01:23:04.989
Morning, Mr. Church.

01:23:07.560 --> 01:23:09.153
Mr. Church?

01:23:15.040 --> 01:23:16.633
Mr. Church?

01:23:18.160 --> 01:23:19.309
Hey.

01:23:19.440 --> 01:23:22.432
Hey, I'm just resting.

01:23:22.520 --> 01:23:24.193
Just resting.

01:23:39.400 --> 01:23:42.677
Mama, where's Mr. Church?

01:23:42.760 --> 01:23:45.479
He's sleeping.

01:23:45.560 --> 01:23:47.119
Sleeping?

01:23:47.200 --> 01:23:49.316
He never sleeps.

01:23:49.400 --> 01:23:51.676
Of course he does, baby.
Everybody sleeps.

01:23:56.240 --> 01:23:57.958
I'll make breakfast.

01:23:58.040 --> 01:24:00.873
- You?
- Yes, me.

01:24:03.360 --> 01:24:06.591
<i>I told work I wouldn't be
coming in anytime soon.</i>

01:24:06.680 --> 01:24:08.193
<i>Mr. Church was on complete bed rest...</i>

01:24:08.280 --> 01:24:11.033
<i>and i2' was my turn
to take care of him.</i>

01:24:13.520 --> 01:24:15.318
<i>Somehow, my hands
were doing the work.</i>

01:24:17.000 --> 01:24:18.991
<i>All those years
watching Mr. Church...</i>

01:24:19.080 --> 01:24:22.152
<i>seemed to have soaked
into my skin, my bones.</i>

01:24:22.240 --> 01:24:24.834
<i>And I knew exactly
what needed to be done.</i>

01:24:24.920 --> 01:24:27.196
<i>I chopped, diced, and minced.</i>

01:24:27.280 --> 01:24:29.317
<i>Mixed, mashed, and beat.</i>

01:24:29.400 --> 01:24:31.676
<i>Stirred, sprinkled,
dashed, and pinched.</i>

01:24:31.760 --> 01:24:33.114
Ready to try?

01:24:34.160 --> 01:24:35.639
It's very hot.

01:24:35.720 --> 01:24:37.233
Be careful.

01:24:46.400 --> 01:24:50.030
<i>And while bread baked,
I sewed.</i>

01:24:50.120 --> 01:24:52.873
<i>And while pies cooled,
I sat at the piano.</i>

01:24:52.960 --> 01:24:55.873
<i>And I realized every talent
Mr. Church had...</i>

01:24:55.960 --> 01:24:57.997
<i>he taught himself
while passing the time...</i>

01:24:58.080 --> 01:24:59.593
<i>caring for someone else.</i>

01:25:03.280 --> 01:25:05.271
- Hey.
- Can I climb up?

01:25:05.360 --> 01:25:07.351
Yes, of course.
Always.

01:25:07.440 --> 01:25:09.670
How's my favorite little girl doing?

01:25:09.760 --> 01:25:12.070
Good.

01:25:12.160 --> 01:25:13.833
Tell me a story.

01:25:13.960 --> 01:25:16.076
Tell you a story.

01:25:16.160 --> 01:25:17.912
Okay.

01:25:18.000 --> 01:25:19.752
Once upon a time...

01:25:19.840 --> 01:25:22.070
They always start that way.

01:25:22.160 --> 01:25:25.278
Well, that's how you know
it's a story, my dear.

01:25:25.360 --> 01:25:30.355
Once upon a time,
there was a little...boy.

01:25:30.440 --> 01:25:32.033
What was his name?

01:25:32.120 --> 01:25:35.636
What would you like
his name to be?

01:25:36.680 --> 01:25:37.875
Henry.

01:25:37.960 --> 01:25:39.314
Like you.

01:25:39.400 --> 01:25:41.789
Well, then Henry it shall be.

01:25:41.880 --> 01:25:45.794
Once upon a time, there was
a little boy named Henry.

01:25:45.880 --> 01:25:49.760
And this boy was afraid
of just about everything...

01:25:49.840 --> 01:25:51.990
except for ladybugs.

01:25:52.120 --> 01:25:54.396
- Ladybugs?
- Ladybugs.

01:25:54.480 --> 01:25:56.312
And one day while he was out...

01:25:56.400 --> 01:25:59.995
a ladybug caught his eye
and he decided to chase it.

01:26:00.080 --> 01:26:02.913
And he chased this ladybug
for so long...

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:05.230
that he actually turned
into a grown man...

01:26:05.320 --> 01:26:06.674
chasing the same ladybug.

01:26:06.760 --> 01:26:11.152
And the ladybug led him
to a little tiny house.

01:26:11.240 --> 01:26:13.800
And in the house,
he found the kindest woman...

01:26:13.880 --> 01:26:16.235
and her beautiful little girl living there.

01:26:16.320 --> 01:26:18.072
And the man told the woman...

01:26:18.160 --> 01:26:19.958
that he apologized for coming
in the house this way...

01:26:20.040 --> 01:26:22.077
but he was following this ladybug...

01:26:22.160 --> 01:26:24.151
and that he looked everywhere
all over the place.

01:26:24.280 --> 01:26:26.191
He couldn't find it no more.

01:26:26.280 --> 01:26:28.476
He promised her that he'd leave.

01:26:28.560 --> 01:26:32.394
But the woman said,
"Don't leave. Stay."

01:26:32.480 --> 01:26:33.879
She said, "Stay here with us."

01:26:34.000 --> 01:26:37.516
She said, "We don't have much,
but everything we got...

01:26:37.600 --> 01:26:39.876
we'll share with you."

01:26:39.960 --> 01:26:42.474
And did he stay?

01:26:42.560 --> 01:26:44.756
He did.
You know why?

01:26:46.880 --> 01:26:51.716
Because for the first time,
he felt safe.

01:26:53.200 --> 01:26:56.318
For the first time,
he wasn't afraid.

01:26:56.440 --> 01:26:58.636
He felt happy-

01:26:58.720 --> 01:27:00.631
And he promised
that if he ever saw...

01:27:00.720 --> 01:27:02.358
that ladybug again...

01:27:02.440 --> 01:27:04.351
that he was going to thank her.

01:27:04.440 --> 01:27:05.953
Did he?

01:27:06.040 --> 01:27:08.714
Not yet.

01:27:08.800 --> 01:27:11.872
He still hasn't stopped looking.

01:27:14.560 --> 01:27:16.471
Maybe she's in the sky.

01:27:20.920 --> 01:27:22.718
Well, you just might be right.

01:27:26.440 --> 01:27:28.351
You just might be right.

01:27:36.080 --> 01:27:38.435
You should be in bed.

01:28:17.280 --> 01:28:19.112
"The blue level
of the Mediterranean...

01:28:19.200 --> 01:28:22.556
"hugged to its calm breast
the victims of all the wars.

01:28:22.640 --> 01:28:25.314
"Calamity is in the tempest
of its history.

01:28:25.400 --> 01:28:27.869
"The breath of the evening breeze
came to cool...

01:28:27.960 --> 01:28:29.553
"with the mulberry tree...

01:28:29.640 --> 01:28:31.916
"which sighed faintly...

01:28:32.000 --> 01:28:34.799
"as if regretting
the passing of this man.

01:28:34.880 --> 01:28:37.713
"This man of dark deeds
but of large heart...

01:28:37.800 --> 01:28:40.314
"who often at noonday
would lie down...

01:28:40.400 --> 01:28:41.720
to sleep under its shade."

01:28:43.640 --> 01:28:45.039
Okay.

01:28:49.880 --> 01:28:51.678
Can I get you something to eat?

01:28:53.520 --> 01:28:54.510
No.

01:28:55.600 --> 01:28:57.830
You want some water?

01:29:00.520 --> 01:29:01.999
No.

01:29:06.440 --> 01:29:09.000
Okay, well, I'll give you
your privacy.

01:29:09.080 --> 01:29:10.354
No.

01:29:14.360 --> 01:29:16.271
I don't want my privacy.

01:30:05.720 --> 01:30:08.917
Mr. Church, I fell asleep
in this armchair.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:13.593
Mr. Church?

01:30:41.960 --> 01:30:43.633
Mr. Church?

01:30:47.680 --> 01:30:49.432
Mr. Church...

01:31:15.680 --> 01:31:17.956
<i>People act strange around death.</i>

01:31:22.320 --> 01:31:23.958
<i>There are those
who talk about everything...</i>

01:31:24.080 --> 01:31:26.151
<i>but the person who died.</i>

01:31:28.000 --> 01:31:31.470
<i>Those who talk about
only the person who died.</i>

01:31:34.040 --> 01:31:35.838
<i>Those who try
to cheer you up.</i>

01:31:38.160 --> 01:31:41.073
<i>And those who can't help
but make you cry.</i>

01:31:48.840 --> 01:31:50.990
<i>And then there are those
who say nothing at all.</i>

01:31:54.360 --> 01:31:56.158
<i>Because they don't have to.</i>

01:32:10.360 --> 01:32:13.512
Yeah, of course.
Thank you so--

01:32:13.600 --> 01:32:16.433
Thank you so much.
Excuse me one second.

01:32:16.520 --> 01:32:17.874
Excuse me.

01:32:19.760 --> 01:32:22.115
- Hi, can I help you?
- Sorry, ma'am.

01:32:22.200 --> 01:32:23.759
Is this Mr. Church's wake?

01:32:23.840 --> 01:32:25.638
Yes.

01:32:25.720 --> 01:32:28.155
I was a friend.
Name's Frankie Twiggs.

01:32:28.240 --> 01:32:29.560
Folks call me Jelly.

01:32:30.600 --> 01:32:31.954
Jelly?

01:32:32.040 --> 01:32:33.519
I'm sorry for, you know,
barging in...

01:32:33.600 --> 01:32:36.194
but we hadn't seen Hands
for quite some time...

01:32:36.320 --> 01:32:37.515
and we done missed him,
and I just--...

01:32:37.600 --> 01:32:38.829
"Hands?"

01:32:38.920 --> 01:32:42.550
Yeah, that's what we called him
on account of...

01:32:42.640 --> 01:32:45.234
He played piano at my bar
for over 30 years.

01:32:45.320 --> 01:32:47.391
So, he worked for you.

01:32:47.520 --> 01:32:49.397
Oh, no, no.
Nothing like that.

01:32:49.480 --> 01:32:51.357
It was more for him, you know?

01:32:51.440 --> 01:32:54.000
One night, he just wandered
over to the piano...

01:32:54.080 --> 01:32:56.310
and then, barn,
he started playing.

01:32:56.400 --> 01:32:58.073
Place lit up.

01:32:58.160 --> 01:33:00.037
I'm telling you,
this cat was good.

01:33:00.120 --> 01:33:02.077
I thought somebody famous
had just walked in...

01:33:02.160 --> 01:33:03.355
to get a drink, you know?

01:33:03.440 --> 01:33:06.671
He was a whole lot of magic.

01:33:08.120 --> 01:33:10.873
I'm Charlie.

01:33:10.960 --> 01:33:13.679
Pleasure to make
your acquaintance, Charlie.

01:33:13.760 --> 01:33:16.149
Izzy?

01:33:16.240 --> 01:33:17.833
Come here, baby.

01:33:17.920 --> 01:33:20.594
I want you to meet
a good friend of Mr. Church's.

01:33:20.680 --> 01:33:22.717
Here, this is Mr. Church's recipe.

01:33:22.800 --> 01:33:24.552
What?

01:33:24.640 --> 01:33:26.756
I didn't know he could cook.

01:33:33.000 --> 01:33:34.673
This is Izzy.

01:33:34.760 --> 01:33:37.274
- Can you say hi, baby?
- Hi.

01:33:37.360 --> 01:33:39.874
This is Mr. Jelly.

01:33:39.960 --> 01:33:41.359
Twiggs.

01:33:51.120 --> 01:33:52.713
<i>Mr. Church once said...</i>

01:33:52.800 --> 01:33:55.553
<i>a book is meant to be read
from beginning to end...</i>

01:33:55.640 --> 01:33:58.712
<i>but is best understood
from end to beginning.</i>

01:34:01.000 --> 01:34:03.833
<i>I suppose everything
does happen for a reason.</i>

01:34:04.960 --> 01:34:06.394
<i>Mama dying.</i>

01:34:06.480 --> 01:34:09.074
<i>Larson saving my baby
and himself.</i>

01:34:09.160 --> 01:34:11.993
<i>Poppy finding a dollhouse
of her own.</i>

01:34:12.080 --> 01:34:13.593
<i>Even Owen...</i>

01:34:13.680 --> 01:34:15.671
<i>the most beautiful 10-year-old boy...</i>

01:34:15.760 --> 01:34:19.310
<i>on this or any other planet
becoming a doctor.</i>

01:35:23.640 --> 01:35:25.313
<i>"Dear Charlotte.</i>

01:35:25.400 --> 01:35:27.550
<i>"You've said you just want
to know me.</i>

01:35:27.640 --> 01:35:31.554
<i>"My dear, you always have.</i>

01:35:31.640 --> 01:35:33.836
<i>"I'm simply a man.</i>

01:35:33.920 --> 01:35:36.070
<i>"Not without faults.</i>

01:35:36.160 --> 01:35:38.151
<i>"That can happen
when you're not the son...</i>

01:35:38.240 --> 01:35:40.231
<i>"your father hoped you'd be...</i>

01:35:40.320 --> 01:35:42.914
<i>"despite his verbal abuse
and beatings.</i>

01:35:45.280 --> 01:35:46.554
<i>"I know you think
I took care of you...</i>

01:35:46.640 --> 01:35:47.994
<i>"and your mother and Izzy...</i>

01:35:48.080 --> 01:35:50.310
<i>"and you gave me nothing
in return.</i>

01:35:52.120 --> 01:35:53.838
<i>"You gave me
the most important thing...</i>

01:35:53.920 --> 01:35:54.990
<i>"life can offer.</i>

01:35:57.760 --> 01:35:59.797
<i>"You gave me a family.</i>

01:36:00.920 --> 01:36:02.991
<i>"And love.</i>

01:36:05.000 --> 01:36:06.593
<i>Henry."</i>

01:36:27.880 --> 01:36:29.518
Mr. Church?

01:36:36.840 --> 01:36:38.353
Henry?

01:36:47.760 --> 01:36:49.398
I'm making eggs and grits, Mama.

01:36:49.480 --> 01:36:51.551
Like Mr. Church showed us.

01:36:51.640 --> 01:36:55.031
Oh, this looks so yummy.

01:36:55.160 --> 01:36:56.594
Thank you.
Thank you.

01:36:56.680 --> 01:36:58.318
Can you set the table for us?

01:36:58.400 --> 01:37:00.630
I can get plates.

01:37:03.680 --> 01:37:07.071
Okay, this will be for me.
This will be for you.

01:37:07.160 --> 01:37:08.798
What do you need?
You're adding a little salt.

01:37:08.880 --> 01:37:10.279
What about cheese?
You need cheese?

01:37:10.360 --> 01:37:11.759
- Yeah.
- Yeah? Here you go.

01:37:14.000 --> 01:37:15.035
More cheese?

01:37:40.600 --> 01:37:42.273
<i>I was wrong when I said...</i>

01:37:42.360 --> 01:37:43.919
<i>the legacy of the Brooks family...</i>

01:37:44.000 --> 01:37:45.673
<i>is having babies out of wedlock.</i>

01:37:46.160 --> 01:37:49.949
<i>The legacy of this family
is Mr. Church.</i>

01:38:12.960 --> 01:38:14.951
<i>Henry Joseph Church
could have been anything...</i>

01:38:15.040 --> 01:38:16.474
<i>he wanted to be.</i>

01:38:17.040 --> 01:38:18.792
<i>He chose to cook.</i>

01:38:19.840 --> 01:38:22.480
<i>The key, he said, jazz.</i>
